FT  06 MAY 92 / Record for Post Office deliveries
A RECORD 89.7 per cent of first-class letters were delivered the day after
postings during the past financial year, Sir Bryan Nicholas, Post Office
chairman, said yesterday.
The figure was an improvement on the previous of 85.5 per cent, beating
targets agreed with the Post Office User's National Council (Pounc), he
said. Pounc welcomed the figures and said it hoped improvements would
continue.
